4
One Move Captures Black (13)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b White to Play.\b0
\par White fills black's eyespace with 1 and black separates the white stones from the outside by descending at 2. This seems to be a strong move, however, black 2 is a mistake.
\par
\par Now, there is a move for white which can kill black's group. How should white play?
\par }
