Diagram 2 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White 1 is a powerful move.
\par If black responds with 2, white cuts black's group in half with 3. Black can't play dansu from either direction due to a shortage of liberties. Black is completely trapped.
\par
\par In the sequence, instead of 2, if were to play at 3, white plays at 2 and that's it. White 1 is the vital point.
\par }
