Diagram 3 (Black's Correct Move)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par In the beginning, when white plays 1, it is correct for black to hane with 2.
\par Then white blocks at 3 and black plays at B4, creating a pae.
\par
\par In the initial diagram, Black 2 is a big mistake as it gives white the opportunity of making a clean capture, when a pae should be white's result.
\par }
